adjectives.description: attenuated (comparative more attenuated, superlative most attenuated)

entries.meaning: Made, or become weak; subject to attenuation.
examples: He had his tea and hot rolls in a morning, while we were battening upon our quarter-of-a-penny loaf — our crug — moistened with attenuated small beer, in wooden piggings, smacking of the pitched leathern jack it was poured from.

entries.meaning: simple past tense and past participle of attenuate
